<div class="faq" style="border-top:none;padding-top:3.5rem">
  <div class="faq-inner">
    <div class="faq-list">
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">How do I join Steyning Town FC?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Complete the registration form on our website and the relevant team manager will contact you with next steps. If the age group is full, you'll be added to a waiting list. We serve Steyning, Bramber, Henfield, Upper Beeding, Washington, Storrington and surrounding West Sussex villages. Email <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a> with any questions.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">What league does Steyning Town FC play in?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">The Men's First Team compete in the <strong>Pitching-In Isthmian League South East Division</strong> for 2026-27, after winning the SCFL Premier Division title in 2025-26. The Women's First Team play in the London &amp; South East Regional Women's Football League (Division One South). The club also has teams in the Horsham &amp; District Youth FL, Sussex County Women &amp; Girls FL, and Sussex Sunday Football League.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">Where does Steyning Town FC play?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Home games are played at the <strong>Peter Humphreys Memorial Ground, Shooting Field, Steyning, West Sussex, BN44 3RQ</strong>. The ground is accessible from the A283, with free parking on site. The facility features a £450,000 3G all-weather pitch (FA &amp; FIFA accredited) and a refurbished clubhouse with bar.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">How much does it cost to watch? Is there parking?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Men's First Team: <strong>Adults £10 · Concessions £6 · Under 16s free.</strong> Women's First Team: <strong>£3 for all · Under 16s and concessions free.</strong> Free parking is available at Shooting Field.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">What is the Development Centre?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">The Development Centre offers after-school football coaching for <strong>boys and girls aged 3–15</strong> on the 3G pitch at Shooting Field. Sessions run Monday–Friday from 3:45–4:45pm and cost <strong>£10 per session</strong>. They're led by qualified coaches including the first team manager. Individual 1-to-1 coaching is also available. Open to players already registered with the club and newcomers alike.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">Can I hire the pitch or clubhouse?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Yes. The <strong>3G pitch</strong> is available for hire — especially weekdays and during summer. Contact Gerry for availability. The <strong>Clubhouse</strong> can be booked for private parties, corporate events, anniversaries, live music, and children's football parties (with 3G pitch + party tea). Email <a href="mailto:theclubhouse.steyning@gmail.com">theclubhouse.steyning@gmail.com</a> to enquire.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">What kit does my child receive and what are the fees?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Every registered player receives a <strong>full playing strip</strong> (shirt, shorts and socks) — the kit remains club property. Annual fees for 2025-26 are: Mini-Kickers to U7 <strong>£200</strong> · U8–U10 <strong>£280</strong> · U11–U12 <strong>£300</strong> · U13–U18 <strong>£320</strong>. Girls' fees are lower to encourage participation. Financial assistance is available — contact the chairman or welfare officer in confidence.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">When was Steyning Town FC founded?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">Steyning Town FC was founded in <strong>1892</strong> as simply "Steyning" and became a founding member of the West Sussex Football League in 1896. The club became Steyning Town Community FC in 2013 after merging with Steyning Strikers Juniors, growing to 18+ teams at the time. Today the club runs 30+ teams with 500+ registered players and holds ★★ England Football accreditation.</p></div>
      </div>
      <div class="faq-item">
        <button class="faq-q" aria-expanded="false"><span class="faq-qt">What is the away kit colour?</span><span class="faq-icon"><svg viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path d="M7 10l5 5 5-5z"/></svg></span></button>
        <div class="faq-a"><p class="faq-at">The 2026–27 away kit is <strong>blue and black</strong>, produced by Edge Teamwear. The home kit features the club's traditional red and white vertical stripes. For kit orders or sizing enquiries, email <a href="mailto:steyningtownfc@gmail.com">steyningtownfc@gmail.com</a>.</p></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
